00:06:11,105 --> 00:06:12,637
narrator: a chocolate truffle cake     

93
00:06:12,639 --> 00:06:15,641
has nothing to do with those rare and pricey fungi              

94
00:06:15,643 --> 00:06:17,176
that are a culinary delicacy,  

95
00:06:17,178 --> 00:06:20,179
nor is it directly related to the chocolate truffle,    

96
00:06:20,181 --> 00:06:23,449
a decadent confection consisting of a chocolate ganache center  

97
00:06:23,451 --> 00:06:25,050
coated in either chocolate,   

98
00:06:25,052 --> 00:06:27,753
cocoa powder, or toasted, chopped nuts.    

99
00:06:31,325 --> 00:06:34,860
a chocolate truffle cake has many variations.       

100
00:06:34,862 --> 00:06:36,128
this version features      

101
00:06:36,130 --> 00:06:39,131
a flourless chocolate truffle cake base        

102
00:06:39,133 --> 00:06:41,733
under a layer of chocolate marble cheesecake,           

103
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:43,769
garnished with fudge ganache.  

104
00:06:46,073 --> 00:06:49,742
to make the cheesecake layer, they begin with cream cheese.  

105
00:06:49,744 --> 00:06:52,811
they mix for three or four minutes to soften it,      

106
00:06:52,813 --> 00:06:55,414
then blend in sugar and salt.  

107
00:06:57,752 --> 00:06:59,685
next, they add sour cream    

108
00:06:59,687 --> 00:07:02,888
to make the cheesecake creamier and fluffier.      

109
00:07:05,826 --> 00:07:08,226
the last ingredients are whole eggs          

110
00:07:08,228 --> 00:07:11,096
blended with vanilla extract.  

111
00:07:11,098 --> 00:07:16,035
another three to four minutes of mixing completes the batter.             

112
00:07:16,037 --> 00:07:18,036
to make the chocolate truffle cake base,            

113
00:07:18,038 --> 00:07:22,641
they combine water, sugar, corn syrup, and cream of tartar,             

114
00:07:22,643 --> 00:07:24,075
which is a leavening agent    

115
00:07:24,077 --> 00:07:27,713
that works in flourless cakes like this one.          

116
00:07:27,715 --> 00:07:30,048
it also prevents the sugar they just added    

117
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:31,917
from crystallizing.       

118
00:07:31,919 --> 00:07:34,787
while heating those ingredients to a boil,      

119
00:07:34,789 --> 00:07:37,655
they soften butter in a mixer,  

120
00:07:37,657 --> 00:07:40,191
then add melted semisweet chocolate,       

121
00:07:40,193 --> 00:07:42,361
which contains vanilla extract.            

122
00:07:45,066 --> 00:07:46,999
they mix for another five minutes or so        

123
00:07:47,001 --> 00:07:50,803
until the chocolate is thoroughly blended in.    

124
00:07:50,805 --> 00:07:53,872
then they add the boiled ingredients,     

125
00:07:53,874 --> 00:07:55,374
then coffee syrup...       

126
00:07:57,878 --> 00:08:01,413
...then blended whole eggs.   

127
00:08:01,415 --> 00:08:04,149
a final five minutes of mixing,     

128
00:08:04,151 --> 00:08:08,487
and the chocolate truffle cake batter is ready.      

129
00:08:08,489 --> 00:08:09,888
they pump it into        

130
00:08:09,890 --> 00:08:12,157
the funnel-shaped feeder of a depositor.         

131
00:08:16,030 --> 00:08:19,631
workers meanwhile line aluminum cake pans with silicone            

132
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:21,767
and place them on a conveyor belt.       

133
00:08:25,439 --> 00:08:27,306
the depositor is set up to squirt            

134
00:08:27,308 --> 00:08:30,642
exactly 28 ounces of the thick chocolate truffle cake batter  

135
00:08:30,644 --> 00:08:33,178
into each pan.          

136
00:08:38,185 --> 00:08:39,785
they pump the thinner cheesecake batter        

137
00:08:39,787 --> 00:08:42,454
to the feeder of a second depositor,      

138
00:08:42,456 --> 00:08:45,190
which squirts an identical amount of cheesecake batter   

139
00:08:45,192 --> 00:08:47,392
into the pan.          

140
00:08:47,394 --> 00:08:48,861
this batter is much lighter   

141
00:08:48,863 --> 00:08:50,795
than the dense chocolate truffle cake batter.       

142
00:08:50,797 --> 00:08:52,664
so rather than blend,      

143
00:08:52,666 --> 00:08:55,067
the two batters form separate layers.         

144
00:08:57,938 --> 00:08:59,538
using the squeeze bottle,    

145
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:02,374
they drizzle on some extra chocolate truffle cake batter  

146
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,147
and drag a knife back and forth,             

147
00:09:09,149 --> 00:09:11,149
creating what's known in pastry making         

148
00:09:11,151 --> 00:09:13,185
as a napoleon-style design.   

149
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:20,893
they put the pans in the oven  

150
00:09:20,895 --> 00:09:25,497
for 90 minutes at 90 degrees fahrenheit.    

151
00:09:25,499 --> 00:09:28,566
the long baking time at a relatively low temperature           

152
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:30,235
ensures the heat penetrates   

153
00:09:30,237 --> 00:09:32,837
the dense truffle batter gradually.        

154
00:09:32,839 --> 00:09:35,040
otherwise, the outside of the cake would burn      

155
00:09:35,042 --> 00:09:37,342
before the inside is fully baked.         

156
00:09:39,847 --> 00:09:42,181
the cakes cool at room temperature,       

157
00:09:42,183 --> 00:09:44,516
then go into a freezer overnight.       

158
00:09:44,518 --> 00:09:45,984
the next day, workers      

159
00:09:45,986 --> 00:09:49,254
easily pop the rock-solid cakes from the pans          

160
00:09:49,256 --> 00:09:52,724
thanks to that silicone liner.  

161
00:09:52,726 --> 00:09:57,196
they place the cake on a cardboard circle,      

162
00:09:57,198 --> 00:09:58,397
then, with a pastry bag,     

163
00:09:58,399 --> 00:10:02,801
garnish the edge with fudge ganache.       

164
00:10:02,803 --> 00:10:05,137
the ganache is made of heavy cream,         

165
00:10:05,139 --> 00:10:07,606
corn syrup and the same melted chocolate         

166
00:10:07,608 --> 00:10:09,441
they put in the truffle cake batter.           

167
00:10:11,811 --> 00:10:14,480
they placed the finished chocolate marble truffle cake  

168
00:10:14,482 --> 00:10:17,482
into an automatic cake slicer.  

169
00:10:17,484 --> 00:10:21,019
the turntable rotates after each strike of the blade     

170
00:10:21,021 --> 00:10:25,090
until the machine has cut the cake into 12 slices     

171
00:10:25,092 --> 00:10:27,726
and separated them with paper dividers.       

172
00:10:30,831 --> 00:10:33,031
they wrap the cake in a cardboard band       

173
00:10:33,033 --> 00:10:35,000
printed with the brand name.   

174
00:10:40,641 --> 00:10:42,908
then they put the dessert through a machine,        

175
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:45,710
which encases the cake in plastic film,         

176
00:10:45,712 --> 00:10:48,280
then applies heat to shrink the film taut.     

177
00:10:53,921 --> 00:10:56,054
to serve this decadent dessert,            

178
00:10:56,056 --> 00:10:57,656
you let it defrost at room temperature       

179
00:10:57,658 --> 00:10:59,391
for four to five hours      

180
00:10:59,393 --> 00:11:02,126
or in the fridge overnight.   

181
00:11:02,128 --> 00:11:04,395
impatient chocoholics take note --           

182
00:11:04,397 --> 00:11:07,332
you can also defrost a slice in the microwave     

183
00:11:07,334 --> 00:11:08,867
in just 30 seconds.       

184
